*] Ansible Content Collections :- is a set of related roles, modules and plugins that may be used in the playbook .

    Examples:

        redhat.insight :- contains roles, modules and plugin that used to register system with redhat insights for RHEL
        cisco.ios:- contains roles, modules and plugin used to manage Cisco IOS network appliances.

    You can install a selected version of collection , so you have all the roles , modules and plugin that can be uses in the playbook

    Namespace can be used to specify the collection by name , it is the first part of the collection name like:-
        community.crpt
        community.postgresql
        redhat.rvt
        redhat.satellite
        redhat.insights

*] Selecting Source of ansible content collections

    Automation Hub :- contains ansible content collections that certified from redhat.
                      you should have subscription to ansible automation platform to access this.
    Private Automation Hub :-
    Ansible Galaxy :- community support
    Third party [Git Repositories or Archive File]

*] Before you use any module from the Collections you need to install it first
    ansible-galaxy collection install community.mysql -p collections
    You can also install collections from requirements.yml file

    ---
    collections: 1
      - name: community.crypto 2

      - name: ansible.posix
        version: 1.2.0 3

      - name: /tmp/community-dns-1.2.0.tar.gz 4

      - name: http://www.example.com/redhat-insights-1.0.5.tar.gz 5

      - name: git+https://github.com/ansible-collections/community.general.git 6
        version: main

    ansible-galaxy collection install -r collections/requirements.yml -p collections

*] By default ansible-galaxy download the collections from ansible galaxy website if you need to make automation hub first
   update ansible.cfg file by the below

   [galaxy]
   server_list = automation_hub, galaxy  1

   [galaxy_server.automation_hub]
   url=https://console.redhat.com/api/automation-hub/  2
   auth_url=https://sso.redhat.com/auth/realms/redhat-external/protocol/openid-connect/token 3
   token=eyJh...Jf0o 4

   [galaxy_server.galaxy]
   url=https://galaxy.ansible.com/